page.title: 17 ROSEBERRY GREEN
page.content: Roseberry Green was built in 1973 and it was made to look old.It is situated between Richardson's Farm and the church.It is made of a mixture of styles.There are 2 detatched houses and 11 terraced. There are 14 slate roofs including garages and 21 pantiles and one other type. There are 5 houses built in limestone brick, 12 stone walls, 12 brick and 3 houses have rendered walls including garages. The residents haveto maintain the green . When the houses were built the pond was made deeper and wider.Ducks started to nest there.At the bottom there are lots of weeds and tadpoles swim at the edge of the pond.There is a stream at the other side of the road and the stream runs under the road and in to the pond.There are lots of other fresh water animals.
